==== Central Catecholamine Deficiency (Chapter @ch:neurological)

    - Abnormally low CSF levels of norepinephrine, dopamine, and DHPG (3,4-dihydroxyphenylglycol)
    - Catecholamine levels correlated with grip strength, effort preference, and cognitive symptoms
    - First direct CSF neurotransmitter measurements in ME/CFS

